The music player needs notification permission to allow the app to display a music playback interface in notifications on the home screen or lock screen (from Android 13 onwards). This helps display song titles, artist names, and playback controls (such as pausing, skipping songs, etc.) without needing to open the app. If you deny this permission, you won't receive or be able to control notifications from the app, but other features will continue to work normally.
